
[1]salutation

   SALUTA'TION, n. [L. salutatio. See Salute.]

   The act of saluting; a greeting; the act of paying respect or reverence
   by the customary words or actions; as in inquiring of persons their
   welfare, expressing to them kind wishes, bowing, &c. Luke 1. Mark 12.

   In all public meetings and private addresses, use the forms of
   salutation, reverence and decency usual among the most sober people.
